Epigyne (
Fig. 2I
, 
3B
): often covered anteriorly by strong, dark plugs, densely covered by thick plumose hairs (
Fig. 2J
). Almost circular, posteriorly reaching epigastric furrow. Although barely noticeable as part of epigyne due to less pronounced sclerotization, there are two ear-shaped lateral shallow depressions (ESD in 
Fig. 2I
) ending posteriorly on semi-circular hoods of copulatory openings (Ho and CO in 
Fig. 2K
). Median septum shows flanks appearing flat and wing-like anteriorly (
Figs 2I, K
, MS in 
Fig. 3B
). Visible first half of copulatory duct forms inverted U-shape (
Fig. 2I
).

Habitat. Aleppo pine forest (
Pinus halepensis
) and immediate surroundings, within typical salt marshes of the Bardenas area.
